{"article_id":"k5hlYr3VNIJ7HPtM","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The coronavirus does not discriminate ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"but people do .","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"The coronavirus is not partisan ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"but politicians are .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"When we should be coming together","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"to address a shared crisis ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"some are intent on driving us apart","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"and exacting partisan advantage in the midst of the crisis .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"Across the country , Republicans are intensifying their efforts","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"to make it harder to vote ,","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"with particular focus on suppressing the votes of African Americans and other minorities .","depth":4},{"id":11,"text":"With the pandemic making in-person voting dangerous ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"Congress should move rapidly","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"to provide resources","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"to help every state create systems","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"for voting by mail .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"The first rescue package , the CARES Act , included some money for vote-by-mail programs ,","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"but far short of what is needed .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"Columnists","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"In-depth political coverage , sports analysis , entertainment reviews and cultural commentary .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"Why not provide it ?","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"Republicans are worried","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"that voting by mail may increase turnout , particularly among low-income and minority voters .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"Donald Trump voiced the fear ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"\" They had things , levels of voting ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"if you ' d ever agreed to it ,","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"you ' d never have a Republican","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"elected in this country again. \"","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"Trump said this in March ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"dismissing Democratic efforts","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"to expand mail-in voting ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"make registration easier ,","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"and extend voting days .","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"Republican voters in states","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"that already have widespread vote by mail","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"support the program overwhelmingly .","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"Some sensibly argue","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"that vote by mail might actually help Republicans this fall ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"because older voters","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"- who tend to be more conservative -","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"are more likely to be reluctant to expose themselves to the virus","depth":14},{"id":43,"text":"by going to crowded voting places .","depth":14},{"id":44,"text":"But Republican history ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"grounded in the Southern party base","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"that has always sought to suppress the black vote ,","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"makes them fear efforts","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"to make voting easier for all .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"In Wisconsin , we saw the deadly effects of that .","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"Wisconsin Republicans in control of the state legislature blocked the Democratic governor ' s effort","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"to allow widespread vote by mail in the primary .","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"When state election officials were swamped by a staggering demand for absentee ballots ,","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"they refused to extend the time","depth":15},{"id":54,"text":"for voting ,","depth":15},{"id":55,"text":"ensuring that thousands never received a response to their request for a ballot .","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"At the same time , officials were slashing the number of voting precincts ,","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"worried","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"they ' d lack volunteers","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"to staff them .","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"In Milwaukee , the home of two-thirds of the black population in Wisconsin , the number of polling places was reduced from 180 to five .","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"That guaranteed long lines","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"that surely made it impossible for many still at work to vote","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"and put those","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"who did vote","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"at risk .","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"Dozens","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"who went to vote","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"have since contracted the coronavirus .","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"Simultaneously , conservatives in Wisconsin have joined with Republicans","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"to push purging of voter lists .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"From 2016 to 2018 , Wisconsin purged 14 percent of voters on its rolls","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"( the national average is about 7.6 percent ) .","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"In the most recent round , election officials sent letters to 232,000 voters","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"who would be removed","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"if they did not respond .","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"One in eight voters in Milwaukee were at risk .","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"Voters in black neighborhoods were nearly twice as likely to be flagged as those in white neighborhoods .","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"In Georgia in 2018 , the Republican candidate for governor , Brian Kemp , was serving as the secretary of state .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"He sought to purge 300,000 voters ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"and 53,000 voter registrations were put on hold ;","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"80 percent were people of color .","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"Two hundred voting precincts were closed , most in areas with large black populations .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"The Democratic candidate , Stacy Abrams , lost the race by a margin far less than the votes","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"that were suppressed .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"As she noted ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"\" Especially in states like Georgia ,","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"where diversifying demographics have us on the precipice of transformative political change ,","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"we are seeing Republicans employ voter suppression","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"to limit who has access to the polls .","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"Disproportionately , under GOP secretaries of state , this process affects Democrats , particularly in communities of color .","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"The clear intention is to strip people of their right","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"to vote . \"","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"In state after state , conservative groups are suing to force purges .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"The Trump Justice Department has piled on :","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"a June 2017 letter went to 44 states","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"it would review how the states were planning to \" remove the names of ineligible voters . \"","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"Purging voters ,","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"blocking vote by mail ,","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"requiring official voter ID ,","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"closing precincts ,","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"limiting early voting ,","depth":16},{"id":103,"text":"limiting the hours","depth":19},{"id":104,"text":"that voting booths are open ,","depth":19},{"id":105,"text":"blocking same day or automatic voter registration ,","depth":19},{"id":106,"text":"gerrymandering","depth":20},{"id":107,"text":"to segregate the minority vote","depth":20},{"id":108,"text":"-","depth":17},{"id":109,"text":"the list goes on .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"Voting is the fundamental basis of democracy .","depth":6},{"id":111,"text":"Particularly in times of crisis , it is vital that the people ' s voice be heard .","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"The president and the modern-day Republican Party are convinced","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"if everyone votes ,","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"they will not fare well .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"Think about that .","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"Our last presidential election was marred by foreign intervention and WikiLeaks .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"We couldn ' t stop that .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"But we should not steal from ourselves .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"We can not allow the coming election to be scarred by homegrown intervention and TrickiLeaks .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":241,"left":122,"right":240,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":122,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":240,"left":130,"right":239,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":130,"left":127,"right":129,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":127,"left":123,"right":126,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":123,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":126,"left":124,"right":125,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":124,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":129,"left":128,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":139,"right":238,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":139,"left":136,"right":138,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":134,"right":135,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":11,"right":133,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":133,"left":12,"right":132,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"pare